SET ECHO ON
ECHO ===== INDEX SHAKE-DOWN START =====

DO SANDBOX
WORKSPACE OPEN DBF

ECHO --- Phase 0: Baseline (no assumptions) ---
SELECT students
FIELDS
LIST
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 1: Without any active order (physical order) ---
SETORDER 0
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
BOTTOM
TUP
SKIP -1
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 2: Existing INX (auto-attach behavior) ---
CLOSE
USE students
ECHO (Confirm it auto-attached students.inx in your startup message)
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
SKIP 5
TUP
SKIP -2
TUP
BOTTOM
TUP
SKIP -1
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 3: Ascending vs Descending toggle (should affect ordered nav) ---
ASCEND
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
DESCEND
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
ASCEND
BOTTOM
TUP
DESCEND
BOTTOM
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 4: SEEK / FIND / LOCATE without relying on indexes ---
ECHO Pick a real last name and SID from LIST/TUP and plug in below.

SEEK <LNAME1> IN lname
TUP

FIND <LNAME1> IN lname
TUP

LOCATE lname = "WHITE"
TUP
CONTINUE
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 5: Create a disposable copy for destructive index tests ---
CLOSE
USE students
COPY TO students_idxtest WITH SIDECARS OVERWRITE
CLOSE
USE students_idxtest
COUNT
TOP
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 6: Build a fresh INX (1INX), attach, and navigate ---
ECHO Create a brand new INX:
INDEX ON lname TAG students_idxtest_lname.inx

ECHO Attach it as the active order:
SETINDEX students_idxtest_lname.inx

ASCEND
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
SKIP 10
TUP

DESCEND
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 7: Convert/rewrite to 2INX and repeat nav tests ---
ECHO This should print that it wrote 2INX:
REINDEX students_idxtest_lname.inx

ASCEND
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
SKIP 25
TUP

DESCEND
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 8: Data mutation -> confirm index staleness -> rebuild -> confirm refresh ---
ECHO Change an indexed field; order may become stale until REINDEX.
ECHO Use a value that will sort to an extreme, like ZZZ... or AAA...

TOP
TUP
REPLACE lname WITH "ZZZTEST"
TUP

ECHO Now test ordered behavior (it may be wrong/stale until rebuild):
TOP
TUP
BOTTOM
TUP

ECHO Rebuild index and confirm order updates:
REINDEX students_idxtest_lname.inx
DESCEND
TOP
TUP
ASCEND
BOTTOM
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 9: CNX container build + tags + rebuild ---
ECHO Create CNX container:
CNX CREATE students_idxtest.cnx

ECHO Add tags (field-based tags):
CNX ADDTAG LNAME students_idxtest.cnx
CNX ADDTAG SID students_idxtest.cnx

ECHO List CNX tags:
CNX LIST students_idxtest.cnx

ECHO Build tag data:
REBUILD students_idxtest.cnx

ECHO Attach CNX + set active tag:
SETCNX students_idxtest.cnx
SETORDER students_idxtest.cnx LNAME --asc

TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
SKIP 10
TUP
BOTTOM
TUP

ECHO Switch direction and repeat:
DESCEND
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP

ECHO Switch tag to SID and repeat:
SETORDER students_idxtest.cnx SID --asc
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
BOTTOM
TUP

ECHO Clear order and confirm physical nav still works:
SETORDER 0
TOP
TUP
SKIP 1
TUP
BOTTOM
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 10: CNX search commands (still do, even if SEEK is currently sequential) ---
SEEK LNAME = CLARK
TUP
FIND WHITE IN lname
TUP
LOCATE sid = 50000016
TUP

ECHO --- Phase 11: Cleanup (ERASE removes the test table + its sidecars/index artifacts) ---
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE students_idxtest CONFIRM

ECHO ===== INDEX SHAKE-DOWN END =====
